---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';

const answerLD = JSON.stringify({
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: 'ChatGPT vs Claude: Which Is Actually Better (2026)?',
  author: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'aipedia.wiki Editorial', url: 'https://aipedia.wiki/about/editorial/' },
  publisher: { '@id': 'https://aipedia.wiki/#organization' },
  datePublished: '2026-04-16',
  dateModified: '2026-04-16',
  mainEntityOfPage: 'https://aipedia.wiki/answers/chatgpt-vs-claude-which-is-better/',
});
---

<BaseLayout title="ChatGPT vs Claude: Which Is Actually Better (2026)?" description="ChatGPT wins on multimodal tools and plugins. Claude wins on writing, reasoning, and context length. Honest comparison as of April 2026.">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={answerLD} />
  <Breadcrumb items={[{ label: 'Answers', href: '/answers/' }, { label: 'ChatGPT vs Claude: which is better?' }]} />

  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto py-6">
    <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">ChatGPT vs Claude: which is better?</h1>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-6">
      <a href="/about/editorial/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 no-underline hover:underline">
        <span class="text-[var(--text-secondary)]">aipedia.wiki Editorial</span>
      </a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">·</span>
      <time datetime="2026-04-16" class="text-[var(--accent-success)]">Updated April 2026</time>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-sm max-w-none wiki-prose">
      Claude beats ChatGPT in 2026. It's the top pick for coding, reasoning, and writing, core needs for most knowledge workers.[1][2][4]
      
      Claude Opus 4.6 crushes coding benchmarks at 80.8% on SWE-bench Verified, edging GPT-5.4's 80.0%.[2][4] Functional accuracy hits 95% versus ChatGPT's 85%, meaning less debugging.[4] Its 200K context window handles big codebases better than ChatGPT's 128K, and [Claude Code](/tools/claude-code/), free in the $20/month Pro plan, acts as a terminal agent for multi-file edits and tests.[1][2] Developers pick it 70% of the time for refactoring.[4] Use Claude if you're building software; it's simply more reliable.
      
      ChatGPT shines in everyday extras. It has voice mode, DALL-E images, full web browsing, and a huge [GPTs store](/tools/gpts-store/) ecosystem.[2][4] Both Pro/Plus tiers cost $20/month with similar limits, but ChatGPT's broader tools suit casual users, marketers, or voice brainstorming.[1][2] I rate it fine for quick tasks, but it hallucinates more and writes formulaic prose.[1][5]
      
      Claude wins writing too, natural tone, better flow, elite logic in tests like 1,500-word constraints where ChatGPT flopped.[4][5] GPQA reasoning scores 91.3%.[4] ChatGPT ties or leads only in multimodal fluff.
      
      Pick **Claude** if you need precise code or prose. Grab ChatGPT for gimmicks like voice or browsing. Test both on your workflow, Claude's my daily driver.[2]
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-[var(--border)] text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
      <p>This answer reflects flagship models and pricing as of April 2026. See our <a href="/about/scoring/" class="text-[var(--accent-primary)] no-underline hover:underline">scoring methodology</a> for how we evaluate tools.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
